4x \equiv 5 \mod 7 \Longleftrightarrow 4x = 5 + 7k_1\text{ for some }k_1\in\mathbb Z
7x \equiv 4 \mod 15 \Longleftrightarrow 7x = 4 + 15k_2\text{ for some }k_2\in\mathbb Z
