\mathbb Z
7x\equiv4\pmod {15}=4+15\cdot3=47\implies x\equiv7\pmod {15}\text{ as } (7,15)=1
4\cdot2-7=1,4\cdot2\equiv1\pmod 7\iff \frac14\equiv2\pmod 7
\text{So, }x\equiv\frac54\pmod 7\equiv 5\cdot2\equiv3\pmod 7
15-2\cdot7=1,-2\cdot7\equiv1\pmod {15}\iff\frac17\equiv-2\pmod{15}\equiv13
\text{So, }x\equiv\frac47\pmod{15}\equiv4\cdot13\equiv7\pmod{15} 
